The paper discusses cyber-physical attacks and counter defense mechanisms in the context of the Advanced Metering Infrastructure (AMI) in the smart grid. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses communication networks and smart meters, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses mathematical tools for security analysis and implementation, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
